text.tspan: D: project goals and objectives, project stakeholders, process map, customer requirements and critical-to-quality (CTQ) characteristics, establish the project scope, project charter
M: identify key process metrics, collect relevant data, analyze process capability, create detailed process maps, perform a baseline measurement, identify potential data sources
A: identify root causes of process variation: form hypotheses, verify and prioritize root causes based on impact and feasability, validate findings with stakeholders
I: generate and evaluate potential solutions, implement process improvements, conduct pilot tests, optimize the process, implement control measures to sustain improvements
C: implement: process controls, process monitoring, standard operating procedures, mistake-proofing measures, define key performance indicators (KPIs), develop training programs
